    3.944854930272163*^9, {3.944854964891124*^9, 3.944854969602021*^9}, 
    3.944855005576565*^9, 3.944855038894125*^9, {3.944855126456914*^9, 
    3.9448551274437227`*^9}, 3.9448553521409283`*^9, 3.944855399111858*^9, 
    3.94485551311862*^9, 3.944855664189184*^9, {3.9448561418619823`*^9, 
    3.944856143283825*^9}, {3.944856212108499*^9, 3.944856241249332*^9}, 
    3.944856273211988*^9, {3.944856336779784*^9, 3.944856353593092*^9}, {
    3.944856390487636*^9, 3.944856408816431*^9}, {3.944856448593828*^9, 
    3.944856472733062*^9}, {3.9448565064734373`*^9, 3.9448565264939613`*^9}, 
    3.9448565776260653`*^9, 3.944856766052787*^9, {3.944856813067912*^9, 
    3.9448568225602503`*^9}, {3.9448568626687098`*^9, 
    3.9448569169611588`*^9}, {3.944857106554174*^9, 3.94485710755503*^9}, {
    3.944857920383726*^9, 3.9448579250069103`*^9}, 3.945593339789144*^9, 
    3.9455942714050913`*^9, 3.945594961597398*^9, {3.945595068739881*^9, 
    3.9455951560464277`*^9}, {3.945595192707367*^9, 3.945595277838561*^9}, {
    3.94559538652391*^9, 3.945595410593753*^9}, 3.945602502779622*^9},
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Code",
  FontWeight->"Regular",ExpressionUUID->
  "49cd8f63-b9d3-4f57-90b2-0f8d4bb043d7"],
 "\nMust either use Clear[Subscript] to clear all subscripted variables or ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["K", "1"], "=."}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "99904cce-5846-4198-86fe-66a8ee6f2653"],
 " to clear just ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["K", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1624367e-7ad5-4d96-b6ac-f157afad2969"],
 "\n\nIt is OK to use the same symbol for a constant, one  variable, and two \
variables\nIt is also OK to set A[t,r] = A[t], but  not OK to set  A[t]=A, a \
constant\n     Because if later set A=1, then Mathematica displays A[t] as \
1[t] . \n     In general, to be safe from such idiosyncrasies, I use \
different fonts for the symbols: \n          Regular A[t,r], double-strike \
\[DoubleStruckCapitalC][t,r],  script \[ScriptCapitalA][t], Greek \
\[CapitalAlpha][r] or Gothic \[GothicCapitalC][r]\n          I use symbols \
like  k or Greek \[Alpha]  for constants.  \n          So, \
\[ScriptCapitalA][t] = \[Alpha] and later \[Alpha]=1 is OK.\n\nMathematica \
generally uses  K[1] for the integration dummy variable.\n     To make \
integrals easier to read, I use rulesKr   or  rulesKt \n          This \
changes, for example, \[CapitalBeta][K[1]] dK[1]  to  \[CapitalBeta][\[Rho]] \
d\[Rho]    or   \[ScriptCapitalA][K[1]] dK[1]  to  \[ScriptCapitalA][\[Tau]] \
d\[Tau]\n     Don't use K as a free constant. If later set K=3, then dummy \
variable K[1] \[Rule] 3[1]\n\nFor double integrals, Mathematica generally \
uses K[2] for the outer dummy variable and K[1] for the inner dummy variable.\
\n     To make this readable, I use the substitution /.rulesKKr\n\nWarning: \
for readability of integrals, put /.rulesKr or /.rulesKt ",
 StyleBox["before",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " /.rulesDisp\n     This makes complex expressions with functions of \[Rho], \
\[Sigma], and \[Tau] more readable\n     For example, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
   RowBox[{"-", 
    TemplateBox[{
      RowBox[{
        FractionBox["1", "2"], " ", 
        RowBox[{"(", 
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"-", 
              FractionBox["4", "\[Sigma]"]}], "+", 
            FractionBox[
             SuperscriptBox[
             "\[CapitalBeta]", "\[Prime]", MultilineFunction -> None], 
             "\[CapitalBeta]"], "-", 
            FractionBox[
             
             RowBox[{"2", " ", 
               "\"\\!\\(\\*SuperscriptBox[SubscriptBox[\\(\[GothicCapitalD]\\)\
, \\(4\\)], \\(\[DoublePrime]\\)]\\)\""}], 
             SuperscriptBox[
              SubscriptBox["\[GothicCapitalD]", "4"], "\[Prime]", 
              MultilineFunction -> None]], "-", 
            FractionBox[
             RowBox[{"4", " ", "\[CapitalBeta]", " ", 
               RowBox[{"(", 
                 RowBox[{
                   RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"-", "2"}], " ", 
                    SuperscriptBox["c", "2"]}], "+", 
                   RowBox[{"k", " ", "\[CapitalLambda]", " ", 
                    SubscriptBox["\[GothicCapitalD]", "4"]}]}], ")"}]}], 
             RowBox[{"k", " ", 
               SuperscriptBox[
                SubscriptBox["\[GothicCapitalD]", "4"], "\[Prime]", 
                MultilineFunction -> None]}]], "-", 
            FractionBox[
             SuperscriptBox[
              SubscriptBox["\[GothicCapitalD]", "4"], "\[Prime]", 
              MultilineFunction -> None], 
             SubscriptBox["\[GothicCapitalD]", "4"]]}], ")"}]}], "\[Rho]", 
      "1", "r"},
     "InactiveIntegrate",
     DisplayFunction->(RowBox[{
        SubsuperscriptBox[
         StyleBox["\[Integral]", "Inactive"], #3, #4], 
        RowBox[{#, 
          RowBox[{
            StyleBox["\[DifferentialD]", "Inactive"], #2}]}]}]& ),
     InterpretationFunction->(RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"Inactive", "[", "Integrate", "]"}], "[", 
        RowBox[{#, ",", 
          RowBox[{"{", 
            RowBox[{#2, ",", #3, ",", #4}], "}"}]}], "]"}]& )]}]]], "Print",
  GeneratedCell->False,
  CellAutoOverwrite->False,
  CellChangeTimes->{
