Cell[BoxData["\<\"We are imitating the Case 5D_1A methodology. When we plug \
\[CapitalBeta](r) into the remaining equations, they are each even longer \
than in Case 5D_1A, too long to display here. As in Case 5D_1A, we set \
\[Beta]=0 to shorten the equations, and we put the left-hand sides of \
\\!\\(\\*SubscriptBox[\\(R\\), \\(11\\)]\\), \\!\\(\\*SubscriptBox[\\(R\\), \
\\(22\\)]\\), and \\!\\(\\*SubscriptBox[\\(R\\), \\(44\\)]\\) over their \
common denominators, which turn out to be the same common denominator for \
