Cell[BoxData["\<\"There is no algebraic combination of the equations that \
eliminate more than a single integral. However, if we simplify by setting \
\[Alpha]=0, we can solve \\!\\(\\*SubscriptBox[\\(R\\), \\(00\\)]\\) for the \
\\!\\(\\*SubscriptBox[\\(\[GothicCapitalD]\\), \\(4\\)]\\), the remaining \
unknown. But, the expression is a fraction that includes an integral in an \
exponent in the numerator and a double integral in the denominator. Checking \
whether or not the remaining equation, \\!\\(\\*SubscriptBox[\\(R\\), \
\\(11\\)]\\), is an identity when using this expression is too \
computationally intensive for my home computer.\"\>"], "Print",
